<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> "The Rats in the Walls", H. P. Lovecraft, "Bloodcurdling Tales of Horror and the Macabre", p, 8.</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> Quoted in <i>Lovecraft</i>, Carter, p. 45.</li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> H.P. Lovecraft Letter to Robert E. Howard (August 16, 1932), in <i>Selected Letters 1932-1934</i> (Sauk City, WI: Arkham House, 1976), p.57.</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> "The Woman Who Invented Dark Fantasy" by Gary C. Hoppenstand from <i>Nightmare and Other Tales of Dark Fantasy</i> by Francis Stevens, <a href="/wiki/University_of_Nebraska_Press" title="University of Nebraska Press">University of Nebraska Press</a>, 2004, page xiv. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0803292988" class="internal">ISBN 0803292988</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-PartnersWonder-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-PartnersWonder_27-0" title="">^</a></b> <i>Partners in Wonder: Women and the Birth of Science Fiction, 1926-1965</i> by Eric Leif Davin, Lexington Books, 2005, pages 409-10.</li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.copyright.gov/circs/circ22.html" class="external text" title="http://www.copyright.gov/circs/circ22.html" rel="nofollow">How to Investigate the Copyright Status of a Work- U.S. Copyright Office</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> <a href="ftp://rtfm.mit.edu/pub/usenet/news.answers/law/copyright/faq/part2" class="external text" title="ftp://rtfm.mit.edu/pub/usenet/news.answers/law/copyright/faq/part2" rel="nofollow">Copyright Basics by Terry Carroll 1994</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> William Johns, 'Lovecraft Copyright', archived at <a href="http://phantasmal.sourceforge.net/Innsmouth/LovecraftCopyright.html" class="external free" title="http://phantasmal.sourceforge.net/Innsmouth/LovecraftCopyright.html" rel="nofollow">http://phantasmal.sourceforge.net/Innsmouth/LovecraftCopyright.html</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
